The issue you are encountering is related to the encoding of the XML file. The file is encoded as UTF-8, but it contains characters that are not valid in UTF-8, specifically the "smart quote" characters. These characters are causing the MalformedByteSequenceException that you are seeing when trying to parse the file with Xerces.

To resolve this issue, you can try the following steps:

1. Remove the "smart quote" characters from the XML file using a text editor that supports UTF-8, such as Notepad++. This will ensure that the file is properly encoded and can be parsed by Xerces.
2. Use the following code to load the XML file into a String using the correct encoding:
```java
File file = new File("ccd.xml");
byte[] ccdBytes = org.apache.commons.io.FileUtils.readFileToByteArray(file);
String ccdString = new String(ccdBytes, Charset.forName("UTF-8"));
```
This code uses the `FileUtils.readFileToByteArray()` method to read the XML file as bytes, and then creates a new String object using the `Charset.forName("UTF-8")` method to ensure that the string is properly encoded as UTF-8.

1. Once you have the XML string, you can use the `load()` method of the `DocumentBuilder` class to parse the XML document:
```java
DocumentBuilderFactory dbf = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
DocumentBuilder db = dbf.newDocumentBuilder();
Document doc = db.parse(new InputStreamReader(new ByteArrayInputStream(ccdString.getBytes("UTF-8"))));
```
This code creates a new `DocumentBuilder` object and uses the `parse()` method to parse the XML string into a document object. The `InputStreamReader` class is used to read the string as an input stream, and the `getBytes("UTF-8")` method is used to convert the string to a byte array before passing it to the `InputStreamReader`.

Note that the `load()` method of the `CDAUtil` class is not recommended for parsing XML files, as it is not guaranteed to work correctly with all types of XML documents. It is recommended to use the `DocumentBuilder` class instead.
